The reason this is striking is that in the original crystal, there's plenty of energy

40:40.360 --> 40:43.600
in the crystal as a whole to break the bonds.

40:43.600 --> 40:45.480
But the energy is too diffuse.

40:45.480 --> 40:49.360
And so by itself, it can't concentrate to rupture a bond.

40:49.360 --> 40:53.880
The thing that causes the fracture to propagate in an orderly way instead of happening at

40:53.880 --> 40:59.840
random everywhere is that the stress field in the surround, as it deforms, pulls the

40:59.840 --> 41:05.720
stress from the bulk back down to atomic diameters and concentrates it.

41:05.720 --> 41:09.320
This is what hydrothermal vents are doing for the Earth battery, because the battery

41:09.320 --> 41:12.640
is accumulating over the entire atmosphere and interior.

41:12.640 --> 41:17.120
But it's being focused at the regions where rock contacts water and the regions where

41:17.120 --> 41:20.600
the altered water remixes with seawater.

41:20.600 --> 41:25.200
Now I want to show you that this is actually what the citric acid cycle does within chemistry.

41:25.200 --> 41:29.600
It performs a second kind of concentration.

41:29.600 --> 41:35.160
So as the molecule goes around, it pulls in carbon, and then here it splits.

41:35.160 --> 41:37.320
And both parts go back into the cycle.

41:37.320 --> 41:39.800
So where you had one, you now have two.

41:39.800 --> 41:42.520
That's the mathematics of compound interest.

41:42.520 --> 41:47.320
And so you can exponentially grow and you concentrate material within the cycle.

41:47.320 --> 41:52.320
Also like compound interest on an endowment, you can pull molecules off of this to make

41:52.320 --> 41:58.640
your major classes of biological matter, but the material in the cycle is still available

41:58.640 --> 42:03.600
to serve as a kind of flypaper that continues to pull carbon in over and over again.

42:03.600 --> 42:06.440
So this is the second concentration.

42:06.440 --> 42:12.160
Now the thing, this leads to an important way of thinking about the nature of life.

42:12.160 --> 42:16.320
You could imagine that the optimization of this cycle was something carried out by evolution

42:16.320 --> 42:21.360
later, but I think there's actually a better way to view it.

42:21.360 --> 42:23.400
This cycle is self-amplifying.

42:23.400 --> 42:25.880
It works from the environmental sources of carbon.

42:25.880 --> 42:31.280
It works from the Earth's sources of electrons and everything in the biosphere is made from

42:31.280 --> 42:33.040
it.

42:33.040 --> 42:37.800
The biosphere is what you can make if these are the compounds you have.

42:37.800 --> 42:45.600
And so this is why it becomes the core that organizes the whole rest of metabolism.

42:45.600 --> 42:48.400
So does this give us a complete theory of origins?

42:48.400 --> 42:49.400
Not nearly.

42:49.400 --> 42:51.600
There's a lot of work to be done.

42:51.600 --> 42:58.080
There are many problems to be solved and maybe many generations, maybe centuries of work

42:58.080 --> 43:02.360
before we have a satisfactory theory the way we have a theory of matter, but it fundamentally

43:02.360 --> 43:05.840
changes the way we ask questions.

43:05.840 --> 43:09.520
When Darwin was trying to understand the origin of the world, even though he was a consummate

43:09.520 --> 43:14.280
